scott amendola charlie hunter duo events at stanford scott amendola charlie hunter duo facebook twitter email print add to calendar even though this grooving duo utilizes only drums and guitar their music won t leave you lacking leaders of the early 90s bay area acid jazz scene guitarist charlie hunter and drummer scott amendola blazed new trails that led between jazz and funk pop music and avant garde soundscapes in charlie's seminal band tj kirk the name says it all referring to thelonious monk james brown and rahsaan roland kirk they built a huge following of jazz aficionados who were eager to hear new sounds extreme inventiveness and no small amount of humor the london jazz blog says of the duo modestly hunter doesn t draw attention to his virtuosity his technique is so finely honed that it is easy to overlook how extraordinarily his bass runs counter his simultaneous solos amendola laid into his conventional kit confidently mixing restrained jazz invention with freewheeling power surges on cymbals a lingering backbeat worthy of the late richie hayward or a jb revue and a gleeful urge to roll in hiccupping funk at any opportunity when monday july 18 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where campbell recital hall 541 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $28 general $18 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27965 more info last modified july 15 2011
